name: site
definition: A geographical surface that can be identified on a map

name: process unit
definition: A decomposition of the high level Facility function into more granular sub-functions
note / comment: This facility breakdown structure is decided by the process engineer.

name: area
definition: A geographical surface occupied by a Plant
note / comment: A plant area is created to identify the physical location of an equipment within a plant.

name: commissioning unit
definition: A grouping of tags (if the commissioning unit is at the lowest level in the structure), or sub-commissioning units, by the commissioning discipline
note / comment: This grouping allows one to perform commissioning activities.

name: maintenance unit
definition: A grouping of maintenance system by the maintenance discipline. This grouping allows one to perform maintenance activities

name: maintenance system
definition: A grouping of tags  that can be maintained at the same time
note / comment: Maintenance systems are defined by the maintenance discipline.

name: model part
definition: A type of equipment that is manufactured by a manufacturer
note / comment: A Manufacturer/Supplier's catalogue contains the list of Model Part that a manufacturer can build.

name: company
definition: A legal entity engaged in business as a proprietorship, partnership, corporation, or other form

name: corrosion loop
definition: A grouping of tags with similar operating conditions, e.g. pipe, equipment, .. (i.e., made of similar materials of construction, sharing similar corrosion/degradation rate)
note / comment: Corrosion Loops are created to monitor the corrosions of equipment and thus are important to establish proper inspection strategies.

name: corrosion loop type
definition: A classification of corrosion loops

name: equipment
definition: A physical device designed to perform a function

name: equipment property
definition: A characteristic, or property, that an equipment has

name: model part property
definition: A characteristic, or property, than an equipment model has

name: tag property
definition: A characteristic, or property, that a tag has

name: tag class property
definition: A characteristic, or property, that a tag class has

name: equipment class property
definition: A characteristic, or property, that an equipment class has

name: property picklist
definition: A set of possible values that can be assigned to a property

name: property picklist value
definition: A predefined value that can be assigned to a property, in the context of a property picklist

name: discipline
definition: A branch of knowledge of expertise which is responsible for the content of the deliverable

name: document master
definition: A placeholder that allows a project to identify a particular information content to be created or updated
note / comment: A document master is identified by a document number, and it groups all the document revisions created to mature the information content.An index of document masters is called a Master Document Register (MDR), and it allows a project to plan when the information content will reach a particular status (e.g., AFC, ASB). Remark: The first issuance of the document Mmster will be the baseline plan.  Subsequent issuances will reflect any changes in forecast dates.

name: additional file
definition: A file that makes up a particular document revision.
note / comment: In some circumstances, a particular document revision can be made up of more than one file. Examples include:- Native files- Translations of a document- Large documents that have been split into several smaller filesWhen this is the case, all these files shall be provided as a set of files.

name: transmittal
definition: An exchange of information between two companies

name: construction assembly
definition: A grouping of tags intended to be assembled and installed as a whole
note / comment: Tag modules are created to facilitate fabrication during the project.

name: discipline document type
definition: An identification of what type of document is required for what discipline, and what are their delivery requirements
note / comment: Discipline document type is NOT a distribution list

name: tag
definition: An object designed for performing functional requirements and serving as a specification for equipment

name: property
definition: A type of feature that is used to distinguish and describe tags, equipment, models) or their class
note / comment: Alias attribute, characteristic

name: project
definition: A temporary endeavour undertaken to create an asset or a service

name: plant
definition: An assembly of equipment that perform a physical or chemical process, including production, transportation and storage
note / comment: A Plant represents the high level function to be performed, and during the design, a Plant is decomposed in Process Units and Tags

name: document type
definition: A classification of documents

name: equipment class
definition: A classification of equipment and equipment models, according to its physical assembly of component(s)

name: tag class
definition: A classification of tags according to the functions they are required to perform
note / comment: The requirements for the tag class are expressed through the tag class properties

name: document revision
definition: A user-readable set of data structured in order to be printed and stored as a whole (includes drawings)
note / comment: Disciplines specify the content of the documents delivered.The file provided (See FILE_NAME property) shall be:- The most used rendition (when than one rendition is given for the same document).- The entry point for the document (e.g., the table of content, when the document has been split into multiple files).Remark: - All files generated in PDF format shall be text-searchable with commenting enabled.- All files shall be fully virus checked by the Contractor before submission.

name: purchase order
definition: A commercial document used to request a third party to supply goods or services in return for payment

name: leaf node commissioning unit
definition: A commissioning unit that is at the lowest level in the hierarchical structure of commissioning units

name: tag physical connection
definition: A physical connection between tags
note / comment: This information is primarily used for mechanical completions. For piping this information can be generated from 3D models. For electrical and instrumentation, this information can be generated from design tools.  For pipes, the direction From To is the direction of the flow within the pipe.  For electrical cables, the direction From To is the direction of the electrical current.For drivers (e.g., electrical motor), the Frrom To is the direction of the flow of energy, consistent with ISO15926 and ISO22274.For an instrument having only one connection, the From is the Tag the instrument is mounted on (e.g., the vessel).  For a valve, not causing a line break, the From is the line the valve is mounted on.  For auxiliary equipment (e.g., a filter), the From is the Tag where the auxiliary equipment is mounted on.

name: ISO country
definition: A country, as recognized by ISO in its 3166-1 standard

name: engineering status
definition: A phase of the engineering activities

name: safety critical item group
definition: A classification of tags according to safety requirements

name: ISO currency
definition: A currency, as recognized by the ISO organization in its 4217 standard

name: document status
definition: A status that a document, revision can have during its lifecycle

name: ISO language
definition: A language, as recognized by ISO in its 639-1 standard

name: export control classification
definition: A rule that applies to some goods and services when being exported

name: project stage
definition: A phase through which a project goes from conception to implementation

name: reason for issue
definition: The reason for which transmittals are issued

name: tag class equipment class relationship
definition: An equipment class that can be used to implement the function of a tag class
note / comment: For example a Tag classified as a pump could have an equipment installed classified as a centrifugal pump or a rotary pump but it would not make sense to have a flow transmitter installed as this technology cannot satisfy the functional requirements of a pump

name: coding source
definition: A system that has similarities to CFIHOS, and has been coding the objects relevant to CFIHOS in a different way

name: CFIHOS object equivalent mapping
definition: A code assigned by a coding source to a tag class

name: document type classification
definition: A classification of document types according to their nature

name: requirement standard source
definition: The source that has identified this document requirement and proposed it as a standard

name: asset type
definition: A classification of discipline document types according to the type of asset they refer to

name: document representation type
definition: A classification of the documents according to how they should be represented

name: document format
definition: A format, or package, that has to be used to provide a given type of document

name: document retention period
definition: A duration during which documents of a given type anda given discipline have to be kept
note / comment: This information is expected to be owner / operator specific

name: document review type
definition: A type of review that is required for a document

name: source standard
definition: A standard used to define requirements like engineering, operations, etc
note / comment: In the RDL, this table only contains the entries for public standards.Owners / operators are epxected to download them in their database, and then to complement that list with their own standards.

name: life cycle activity class
definition: A classification of activities in the life cycle of a capital asset

name: application condition
definition: A condition under which some document or data requirements have to be applied

name: quantitative property
definition: A type of feature that (a) is used to distinguish and describe tags, equipments, models or their class (b) is numeric (c) may have an associated unit of measure

name: qualitative property
definition: A type of feature that (a) is used to distinguish and describe  tags, equipments, models or their class (b) may have defined list of values to select from (c) is non-numeric

name: unit of measure dimension
definition: A grouping of units of measure that relate to the same kind of quantity
note / comment: The term kind of quantity is defined and used in ISO 80000.

name: unit of measure
definition: A unit that qualifies the size of a quantity

name: unit of measure synonym
definition: A synonyms that uniquely identifies or represents a unit of measure
note / comment: This has been introduced as it is anticipated that not source standards may use e.g. the same symbol to represent the unit of measure. However a synonym should never point to two different units of measure

name: measurement system
definition: A collection of units of measure related to each other

name: document revision site reference
definition: A reference to a site that is included in a document revision

name: document revision plant reference
definition: A reference to a plant that is included in a document revision

name: document revision process unit reference
definition: A process unit that is referred to in a document revision

name: document revision plant area reference
definition: A facility area that is referred to in a document revision.

name: document revision tag reference
definition: A tag that is referred to in a document revision

name: document revision equipment reference
definition: An equipment that is referred to in a document revision

name: document revision model part reference
definition: A model part that is referred to in a document revision

name: document revision purchase order reference
definition: A purchase order that is referred to in a document revision

name: document revision cross reference
definition: A reference to a document revision in another document revision

name: document revision project reference
definition: A project that is referred to in a document revision

name: storage media
definition: A type of technology used to store some documents

name: tag or equipment class property application condition
definition: A condition that applies to the capture or supply of a tag or equipment class property
note / comment: If there are no application condition for the supply of a tag or equipment class property then the value of the property should be supplied.

name: tag or equipment class
definition: A tag class or an equipment class
note / comment: A tag or equipment class can be at the same time a tag class and an equipment class. The two are not mutually exclusive.

name: tag or equipment class synonym
definition: An alternate name used to designate a tag or equipment class

name: tag or equipment class source standard
definition: A tag or equipment class whose engineering information is documented in a source standard

name: non abstract tag or equipment class
definition: A tag or equipment class that is not marked as abstract

name: tag or equipment class property
definition: A characteristic, or property, that a tag or equipment class has

name: tag or equipment class required discipline document type
definition: A discipline document type that is required to be delivered for a specific tag or equipment class

name: data type
definition: A classification of data elements according to their nature

name: application condition group
definition: A grouping of application conditions, that have all to be satisfied to be able to say the condition group is satisfied.
note / comment: An application condition group returns a value true if all the application conditions associated with it are true.The same application condition group can be used for mutiple mappings of tag or equipment classes to source standards.

name: comparison operator
definition: An operator that compares one expression with another
note / comment: The result of the comparison can be True, False, or Unknown.Comparison operators include the typical ones, recognized by all DBMSes, but also entries like IN, to check if the left member of the comparison is present in a list of values, separated by semicolon, in the right member of the comparison.\fs22\f0\fs16

name: application condition group member
definition: An application condition that is used as a component, or member of an application condition group

name: document and data requirement type
definition: A classification of the document and data requirements according to when / by whom the information is generated

name: document and data requirement group
definition: A classification of the document and data requirements according to their nature
note / comment: This classification originates from JIP33.

name: event type
definition: A classification of events that are used as reference in the handover of information for capital facility projects

name: submission reference date
definition: A reference date or point in time vs which some actions need to be accomplished

name: source standard document and data requirement condition
definition: The application of a given condition to a source standard document and data requirement

name: purchase order item
definition: An item on a purchase order
note / comment: The tag, not the model, are necessarily known at the time the pruchase order is place. But the specifications of what is needed are known, and hence the equipment class is know.

name: purchase order item tag
definition: A tag, or part of it, as covered in a purchase order item

name: vendor document
definition: A document, originating from a vendor
note / comment: Alias vendor document schedule

name: purchase order item vendor document and data requirement
definition: A vendor document and data requirement (VDDR) deemed to be appropriate jointly by the purchaser and the vendor for a given purchase order.

name: purchase order item expected event
definition: An event, other than the purchase or the delivery, that needs to be monitored for the delivery of the requirements

name: purchase order item for model part
definition: A purchase order item for a model or a part

name: purchase order item for bulk
definition: A purchase order item for some goods in bulk

name: purchase order item for tag
definition: A purchase order item that refers to one or more tags

name: process class
definition: A classification of the process activities according to the type of action / operation being performed
note / comment: DEXPI and ISO15926 provide good starting points for the list of process classes

name: process class tag class relationship
definition: A tag class that can be used to implement a process activity belonging to a process class

name: process class property
definition: A property that should be specified for process activities related to this process class

name: process activity
definition: A set of actions by which material, energy or information is transformed, transported or stored
note / comment: Processes can be decomposed in sub processes, also known as process steps.

name: process activity tag relationship
definition: A tag that implements (part of) the functional requirements of a process activity

name: process design property
definition: A property that is required by a given process activity
note / comment: This property is often the result of some governing case, to allow for all possible scenarios to be taken into account.

name: stream class
definition: A classification of the process streams according to what is being moved

name: process stream
definition: A flow of material, energy or information produced by one process activity and consumed by another process activity
note / comment: A process stream depicts the interaction between process activities.

name: stream class property
definition: A property that should be specified for process streams related to this stream class

name: process stream property
definition: A property that is required for a process stream

name: process case
definition: A scenario of how processes and streams would perform under some conditions

name: process stream in case
definition: A process stream included in the scope of a case

name: process stream property in case
definition: A process stream property, in the context of a case

name: process activity in case
definition: A process activity included in the scope of a case

name: process property in case
definition: A property of a process activity, in the context of a case

name: source standard document and data requirement
definition: A requirement for document or data, as expressed in a source standard, irrespective of the equipment class
note / comment: These  Document and Data Requirements are of two kinds:  - Design: Information generated during the design activity that has to be approved and reviewed by the purchaser.  - Equipment: Information generated by the equipment manufacturer.This entity represents how to best manage this data, as all document and data requirements expressed in a standard are independent of the equipment classess the standard is coveringIn the RDL, this table only contains the entries for document and data requirements as expressed in public standards.Owners / operators are expected to download them in their database, and then to complement that list with their own document and data requirements for their standards..

name: handover event
definition: A phase, a moment, at which handover of information is taking place

name: discipline document type handover requirement
definition: An indication of the status that a document type should have, if any, at a given handover phase, for a given discipline

name: native file delivery timing
definition: An indication of when the native file should be available

name: deliverable format
definition: A format required to be used by the supplier of information in conformance with JIP33 standard
